                            <comment id="16153040" author="erickerickson" created="Tue, 5 Sep 2017 02:17:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This code has been re-worked recently with the move to pluggable transient cores, see: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8906&quot; title=&quot;Make transient core cache pluggable.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8906&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-8906&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. There was a problem with the test, I suspect 8906 and associated changed the return from the loaded core list and since this test was BadApple&apos;d I didn&apos;t fix it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, 250 iterations later and this test succeeds so I&apos;m removing the @BadApple and we&apos;ll see what happens on Jenkins.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
